headline: New election rules spice up Paris, Marseille and Lyon mayor races
description: The voting system in France's three largest cities will change in the March municipal elections, allowing voters to cast their ballots directly for central city councilors. The novelty has disrupted the political balance and made traditional strongholds less essential.

Iran-US talks expected Thursday despite fears of strikes
description: Iran's Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi said on Sunday that details of a possible deal to forestall fresh conflict were being drawn up ahead of Thursday's renewed talks on Tehran's nuclear program.

headline: India, world's leading dairy producer, struggles to rid market of adulterated milk
description: Water is often added to Indian milk, but so are chemicals and vegetable oils. The quality of Indian dairy is frequently questionable – a fact highlighted by a recent scandal in the state of Gujarat.

headline: Park Chan-wook, director of 'No Other Choice,' still believes in the power of collective values
description: The South Korean filmmaker, known for his keen attention to class struggle, brings a sharp social fable to the screen with his adaptation of Donald Westlake's novel 'The Ax,' laced with biting humor.

headline: Donald Trump's support with 'bro culture' is waning
description: With his racist post about the Obamas, support for immigration police and decision to politicize Puerto Rican singer Bad Bunny's halftime Super Bowl show, the US president has alienated some of his supporters.

In Lyon, the far right pays tribute to activist and tries to avoid controversy
description: Around 3,200 people marched peacefully on Saturday afternoon to condemn 'the far left,' one week after Quentin Deranque's death. The local authorities reported Nazi salutes and racist and homophobic slurs to the courts.

headline: At the Paris Agricultural Show, Macron visits in relative calm
description: In the absence of the traditional breakfast with agricultural unions – some of which boycotted his visit – the president held bilateral talks with the FNSEA and Coordination Rurale. He then toured the exhibition under heavy police protection.

headline: Karyna Shuliak was Jeffrey Epstein's last partner and main heiress. She won't benefit from his will
description: The Belarusian woman met the sexual predator when she was 20 and remained loyal to him until his suicide in prison in 2019.
